CENTRAL = 1
FOLLOW1 = 2
FOLLOW2 = 3

def get_payoff(A, B, R, x_0, T, delta): 
    Q = (1/3) * np.identity(3)
    K_t = Q
    K_sequence = [Q]
    for i in range(T):
        K_t = delta * A.T @ (K_t - K_t @ B @ np.linalg.inv(B.T @ K_t @ B + R / delta) @ B.T @ K_t) @ A + Q
        K_sequence.insert(0, K_t)

    x_t = x_0
    r_ts = []
    payoff = 0
    payoffs = []
    x_ts = [x_0]
    i = 0
    for K in K_sequence[1:]:
        L = -(np.linalg.inv(B.T @ K @ B + R / delta) @ B.T @ K @ A)
        r_t = L @ x_t
        r_ts.append(r_t.item())
        payoff += (-1 * delta**i * (x_t.T @ Q @ x_t)).item() + (-1 * delta**i * (R * r_t**2)).item()
        payoffs.append(payoff)
        x_t_new = A @ x_t + B @ r_t
        x_ts.append(x_t_new)
        x_t = x_t_new
        i += 1
        
    # THE TERMINAL PAYOFF TERM AT TIME T:
    payoff += (-1 * delta**i * (x_t.T @ Q @ x_t)).item()
    payoffs.append(payoff)
        
    return payoff, payoffs, x_ts

def solve(target, x_0, base, delta, T):
    R = 0
    b = 0.01 # the influence weight
    A = np.array([
      [a * [1.0, 1.0-b][target == CENTRAL] for a in base[0]], # central
      [a * [1.0, 1.0-b][target == FOLLOW1] for a in base[1]], # peripheral 1
      [a * [1.0, 1.0-b][target == FOLLOW2] for a in base[2]], # peripheral 2
    ], ndmin = 2)
    B = np.array([
      [[0.0, b][target == CENTRAL]],
      [[0.0, b][target == FOLLOW1]],
      [[0.0, b][target == FOLLOW2]],
    ], ndmin = 2)
    return get_payoff(A, B, R, x_0, T, delta)
In [4]:
def generate_plot(name, x_0, base, delta = 1, T = 30, expected_overlap = False):
    labels = {
        "CENTRAL": "(1) target central agent",
        "FOLLOW1": "(2) target 1st peripheral agent",
        "FOLLOW2": "(3) target 2nd peripheral agent"
    }
    for agent in ["CENTRAL", "FOLLOW1", "FOLLOW2"]:
        payoff, payoffs, _ = solve(globals()[agent], x_0, base, delta, T)
        if expected_overlap and agent != "CENTRAL":
            if agent == "FOLLOW1":
                plt.plot(range(len(payoffs)), payoffs, label = labels[agent], linewidth = 4, color = "orange")
            elif agent == "FOLLOW2":
                plt.plot(range(len(payoffs)), payoffs, label = labels[agent], color = "green")
        else:
            plt.plot(range(len(payoffs)), payoffs, label = labels[agent])
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel("time")
    plt.ylabel("cumulative payoff")
    plt.title(fr"x_0 = {x_0.T[0]}, $\delta$ = {delta}")
    plt.savefig(f"#plots/{name}.png", format = "png", dpi = 300, facecolor= (1, 1, 1))
    plt.show()
In [5]:
def generate_opinions(name, x_0, base, delta = 1, T = 30, expected_overlap = False):
    labels = [
        "x_t^1 agent 1 (central)",
        "x_t^2 agent 2 (peripheral)",
        "x_t^3 agent 3 (peripheral)"
    ]
    for i, agent in enumerate(["CENTRAL", "FOLLOW1", "FOLLOW2"]):
        plt.clf()
        _, _, x_ts = solve(globals()[agent], x_0, base, delta, T)
        for agent_index in range(3):
            plt.plot(range(len(x_ts)), [x_t[agent_index] for x_t in x_ts], label = labels[agent_index])
            
        mapping = {
            "CENTRAL": "(1) central",
            "FOLLOW1": "(2) peripheral",
            "FOLLOW2": "(3) peripheral"
        }
        plt.legend()
        plt.xlabel("time")
        plt.ylabel("agent opinions")
        plt.title(fr"x_0 = {x_0.T[0]}, $\delta$ = {delta}, target {mapping[agent]} agent")
        plt.savefig(f"#plots/{name}.png", format = "png", dpi = 300, facecolor= (1, 1, 1))
        plt.show()

from io import BytesIO
from PIL import Image
from IPython.display import HTML
from base64 import b64encode

images = []
x_0 = np.array([[-1., 0.7, 2.]], ndmin = 2).T
for delta in np.linspace(0.1, 1, 40):
    labels = {
        "CENTRAL": "(1) target central agent",
        "FOLLOW1": "(2) target 1st peripheral agent",
        "FOLLOW2": "(3) target 2nd peripheral agent"
    }
    for agent in ["CENTRAL", "FOLLOW1", "FOLLOW2"]:
        payoff, payoffs, _ = solve(globals()[agent], x_0, A_base, delta, 20)
        plt.plot(range(len(payoffs)), payoffs, label = labels[agent])
    plt.legend(loc = 1, framealpha=0.2)
    plt.xlabel("time")
    plt.ylim(-2.02, -1.82)
    plt.ylabel("cumulative payoff")
    plt.title(fr"x_0 = {x_0.T[0]}, $\delta \approx$ {round(delta, 3)}")
    filex = BytesIO()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(filex, format = "png", dpi = 300, facecolor= (1, 1, 1))
    plt.clf()
    plt.close()
    filex.seek(0)
    images.append(filex)

# graphical engine reused from 
# https://github.com/jbrightuniverse/Generalized-Price-of-Anarchy/blob/main/Generalized%20Price%20of%20Anarchy.ipynb
imgs = [Image.open(image) for image in images]
for i in range(20):
    imgs.insert(31, imgs[31])
for i in range(20):
    imgs.append(imgs[-1])
    imgs.insert(0, imgs[0])

masterfilex = BytesIO()
imgs[0].save(fp=masterfilex, format='GIF', append_images=imgs[1:], save_all=True, duration=75, loop=0)
imgs[0].save(fp="#plots/5_center_mild_dynamic.gif", format='GIF', append_images=imgs[1:], save_all=True, duration=75, loop=0)
HTML("<img src='data:image/gif;base64,{0}'/>".format(b64encode(masterfilex.getvalue()).decode('utf-8')))
